nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
FOR BACKGROUND AND EACH SUBJECT
1) 'EmptyLatentImage' (BLUE):
    - Set area size affected by each prompt
    - Image total dimensions will be the same as those of 'Background' prompt. Any 
      coordinates will be in relation to it with top-left corner having 
      coordinates of (0,0). Remember that y increases downwards

2) 'LatentComposite' (CYAN):
    - Set x and y - coordinates of the top-left corner of prompt area
    - Try to avoid x+width or y+height exceeding dimensions of 'Background'

3) 'CondSetArea - First Pass' (ORANGE):
    - Copy 'width' and 'height' from the corresponding 'EmptyLatentImage' (BLUE)
    - Copy x and y from 'LatentComposite' (CYAN)

4) 'CondSetArea - Second Pass' (YELLOW):
    - Set everything excluding strength to the same values as 'CondSetArea - 
      First Pass' (ORANGE) multiplied by the same factor as in HiRes- 
      Fix (eg. if the image after HiRes-Fix will be twice as large as before it, 
      then multiply by 2. It's fine if you can't get the values set exactly, just 
      make sure nothing sticks outside of 'background')

NOTE: Do not make subject areas touch with their borders or they won't blend nicely. Either separate them a bit or make them overlap.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - In order to increase the number of subjects, move the 'Background' group up, then clone the 'Subject' group structure in its place
 - To decrease number of subjects set 'feather' in 'LatentComposite' (CYAN) to 0, set 'strength' in 'CondSetArea - Firt Pass' (ORANGE) and 'CondSetArea - Second Pass' (YELLOW) to 0
